ork fine.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering logging tests**\\n\\nI need to look at the existing tests for logging to determine if the TCK user-code filter might include a class. It seems the answer is no. If we focus on \\\"active dynamic-access class only,\\\" I probably shouldn't touch the `build.gradle` for other existing dynamic classes. It might be related to adding one line, but I shouldn't run any tests myself as per instructions. I must remember that final files shouldn't include tests either.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `org.apache.commons.httpclient.methods.InputStreamRequestEntity`.\n\nChanges:\n- Added dedicated test file:\n  - `tests/src/commons-httpclient/commons-httpclient/3.0/src/test/java/commons_httpclient/commons_httpclient/InputStreamRequestEntityTest.java`\n- Covered public API paths that instantiate the active class and exercise:\n  - automatic buffering via `getContentLength()`\n  - repeatable writes after buffering\n  - known-length direct stream writing\n  - null content validation\n- Added Native Image runtime initialization for the active class in:\n  - `tests/src/commons-httpclient/commons-httpclient/3.0/build.gradle`\n\nI did not run or compile tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03206acaa7e13f5e016a049ab14a0881a09e50d204ceb91f46\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1077, "output": 632, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 23725, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778686629613, "responseId": "resp_03206acaa7e13f5e016a049aa672a081a0b2815d86d6a29bac"}, "toolResults": []}
